ay channel at central rapidity. It is\nevaluated for $p_{\\rm T}>1.3$ GeV/$c$ and $|y|<0.9$, and extrapolated to\n$p_{\\rm T}>0$. The fraction of non-prompt J/$\\psi$ in the inclusive J/$\\psi$\nyields shows no dependence on the charged-particle multiplicity at central\nrapidity. Charm and beauty hadron relative yields exhibit a similar increase\nwith increasing charged-particle multiplicity. The measurements are compared to\nPYTHIA 8, EPOS 3 and percolation calculations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 May 2015 14:50:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Aug 2015 19:49:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-04"}
